42/*
43 * Dictionary support
44 */
45
46#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
47# include <config.h>
48#endif /* HAVE_CONFIG_H */
49#include <am_defs.h>
50#include <fsi_data.h>
51#include <fsinfo.h>
52
53
54static int
55dict_hash(char *k)
56{
57 u_int h;
58
59 for (h = 0; *k; h += *k++) ;
60 return h % DICTHASH;
61}
62
63
64dict *
65new_dict(void)
66{
67 dict *dp = CALLOC(struct dict);
68
69 return dp;
70}
71
72
73static void
74dict_add_data(dict_ent *de, char *v)
75{
76 dict_data *dd = CALLOC(struct dict_data);
77
78 dd->dd_data = v;
79 ins_que(&dd->dd_q, de->de_q.q_back);
80 de->de_count++;
81}
82
83
84static dict_ent *
85new_dict_ent(char *k)
86{
87 dict_ent *de = CALLOC(struct dict_ent);
88
89 de->de_key = k;
90 init_que(&de->de_q);
91 return de;
92}
93
94
95dict_ent *
96dict_locate(dict *dp, char *k)
97{
98 dict_ent *de = dp->de[dict_hash(k)];
99
100 while (de && !STREQ(de->de_key, k))
101 de = de->de_next;
102 return de;
103}
104
105
106void
107dict_add(dict *dp, char *k, char *v)
108{
109 dict_ent *de = dict_locate(dp, k);
110
111 if (!de) {
112 dict_ent **dep = &dp->de[dict_hash(k)];
113 de = new_dict_ent(k);
114 de->de_next = *dep;
115 *dep = de;
116 }
117 dict_add_data(de, v);
118}
119
120
121int
122dict_iter(dict *dp, int (*fn) (qelem *))
123{
124 int i;
125 int errors = 0;
126
127 for (i = 0; i < DICTHASH; i++) {
128 dict_ent *de = dp->de[i];
129 while (de) {
130 errors += (*fn) (&de->de_q);
131 de = de->de_next;
132 }
133 }
134 return errors;
135}
